156
00:10:38,730 --> 00:10:41,860
That's good. Get all that boring stuff out now.
这样很好 把那些无聊的旧东西抛掉

157
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:45,130
Everything is gonna be fine. Follow my lead, okay?
一切安啦 跟着我就没事，好吗？

158
00:10:45,310 --> 00:10:47,300
All you have to do is pretend to be Mike.
你只要假装是麦克就可以了

159
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:49,470
- I am Mike. - Attaboy.
-我就是麦克啊 -演的真不错

160
00:10:52,610 --> 00:10:54,100
Here they come.
她们来了

161
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:56,480
- I'm Phoebe. - Phoebe. Mike. How you doing?
-我是菲比 -菲比，这位是麦克，你好吗？

162
00:10:56,650 --> 00:10:59,640
- Nice to meet you. - Joey, this is Mary Ellen Jenkins.
-很高兴认识你 -乔伊，这位是犸莉艾伦珍金

163
00:10:59,820 --> 00:11:03,280
So, Mike, how do you and Joey know each other, anyway?
麦克，你跟乔伊是怎么认识的呢？

164
00:11:06,530 --> 00:11:08,960
How do Joey and I know each other?
我跟乔伊是怎么认识的呢？

165
00:11:09,130 --> 00:11:13,260
If I had a nickel for every time somebody's asked me that.
如果每次有人问我这问题 我就有五块钱赚，那我就变富翁了

166
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:16,400
- From school. - We met in college.
-在学校认识的 -我们在大学认识的

167
00:11:19,110 --> 00:11:21,600
I mean high school.
我是说高中

168
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:27,140
You guys go way back, then. So, what are you up to these days?
那你们认识可久了 那你现在是做什么的呢？

169
00:11:27,310 --> 00:11:31,510
- Well, I'm a lawyer. - Mike, attorney at law!
-我是律师 -麦克，律师！

170
00:11:31,820 --> 00:11:34,310
- Actually, I just gave up my practice. - What?
-事实上，我才刚放弃执业 -什么？

171
00:11:34,490 --> 00:11:38,480
That's the kind of thing you usually run by me.
这种事你应该先跟我讨论的

172
00:11:38,990 --> 00:11:43,330
I want to play piano professionally. If I don't do this now, I never will.
我想要成为专业钢琴音乐家 如果现在不赶快做，就来不及了

173
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:45,900
Great. I like that better than the lawyer thing.
太好了，我喜欢音乐家胜过律师

174
00:11:46,070 --> 00:11:50,000
Which is why I waited until now to introduce you to Mike.
这就是为什么我等到现在 才介绍麦克给你

175
00:11:50,170 --> 00:11:52,160
You thought he was still a lawyer.
你不是还以为他是律师吗？

176
00:11:52,340 --> 00:11:55,540
No, that's not what I meant. Let's get you a cocktail.
不，我并没有那样说 我们帮你点杯鸡尾酒吧

177
00:12:00,150 --> 00:12:01,310
What are you doing?
你在做什么呢？

178
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:04,140
Looking for restaurant jobs for you in Tulsa.
帮你在土尔沙找餐厅的工作

179
00:12:04,320 --> 00:12:06,380
That's so sweet. Did you find anything?
真是窝心，有找到吗？

180
00:12:06,550 --> 00:12:09,250
- Slim Pickins. - Nothing, huh?
-速食外餐 -什么都没有，是吧？

181
00:12:09,460 --> 00:12:13,420
No. Slim Pickins. It's a barbecue joint.
不，速食外餐，是间烤肉店

182
00:12:13,590 --> 00:12:17,260
They're looking for a cook. Actually, "cook" may be a bit of a stretch.
他们在找厨师，事实上 并不全然是“厨师”

183
00:12:17,470 --> 00:12:19,990
They're looking for somebody to shovel mesquite.
他们在找炒豆子的帮手

184
00:12:21,470 --> 00:12:23,870
"Slim Pickins"? That is so cheesy.
“速食外餐”？听起来真是不高级

185
00:12:24,040 --> 00:12:26,870
Well, So Cheesy also has an opening.
“布高吉”也有在征人

186
00:12:27,070 --> 00:12:29,870
Honey, that's okay. I know this woman, Nancy..
亲爱的，没关系 我认识一个叫南西的人…

187
00:12:30,040 --> 00:12:33,040
who's a restaurant biz headhunter. She may know something.
她是专门帮餐厅猎人头的 她或许会知道一些职缺

188
00:12:33,210 --> 00:12:35,880
Can I say how much I appreciate you coming with me?
我真的是太感激你愿意跟我去

189
00:12:36,050 --> 00:12:40,990
When we get to Tulsa, I am taking you for a great dinner at Slim Pickins.
当我们抵达土尔沙 我会带你去速食外餐吃大餐的

190
00:12:41,560 --> 00:12:42,580
So Cheesy?
那布高吉呢？

191
00:12:44,490 --> 00:12:46,790
Whole Hog?
全猪餐厅呢？

192
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:51,360
It's gonna be tough to keep kosher in Tulsa.
在土尔沙要找到正式餐厅还真是不简单

193
00:12:55,440 --> 00:12:58,300
Hi, Nancy? Hi, it's Monica Geller.
嗨，南西吗？ 嗨，我是摩妮卡盖勒

194
00:12:58,510 --> 00:13:04,000
I'm good. Listen, I'm looking for a job in Tulsa.
我很好，我需要在土尔沙找份工作

195
00:13:04,380 --> 00:13:07,910
Yeah, well, my husband's been relocated.
是啊，因为我先生被调职到那边

196
00:13:08,080 --> 00:13:10,610
Because I love him.
因为我爱他

197
00:13:11,050 --> 00:13:13,450
No, I don't want a job in New York.
不，我不想要纽约的工作

198
00:13:13,620 --> 00:13:16,820
Javu's looking? Oh, my God!
杰屋在找人？喔，我的天啊！

199
00:13:17,020 --> 00:13:20,980
He asked for me personally? Oh, my God!
他特别指名要我？ 喔，我的天啊！

200
00:13:21,160 --> 00:13:24,620
Wow, this is really, really flattering.
哇，我真的是太受宠若惊了

201
00:13:24,800 --> 00:13:27,630
But I'm moving to Tulsa.
但是我要搬到土尔沙了

202
00:13:27,800 --> 00:13:30,430
So, just, if you would tell Javu..
所以，请你告诉杰屋…

203
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:32,970
I'll take it!
我接受这份工作！

204
00:13:34,040 --> 00:13:37,340
My name's Rachel Greene. I have an appointment for Emma.
我是瑞秋葛林 我有帮艾犸预约看诊

205
00:13:37,550 --> 00:13:41,480
Dr. Gettleman is finishing up with a patient. He'll be out shortly.
葛曼医生快看完病人了 他等一下就会出来

206
00:13:41,650 --> 00:13:45,280
I think you just have a cold. It's definitely not strep.
我想你只是感冒了 没有什么严重性

207
00:13:45,450 --> 00:13:46,780
Thanks, doctor.
谢了，医生

208
00:13:49,620 --> 00:13:53,860
- Would you like a lollipop? - Do you even have to ask?
-要不要来根棒棒糖呢？ -还用问吗？

209
00:13:58,830 --> 00:14:00,960
He is alive!
他还活着！

210
00:14:05,310 --> 00:14:09,110
It's so surprising that you and Joey have known each other for so long..
好奇怪，你跟乔伊认识这么久了…

211
00:14:09,280 --> 00:14:10,940
and I've never heard about you.
而我却从没有听说过你

212
00:14:11,110 --> 00:14:15,480
That's because we had a bit of a falling out.
因为我们有吵过架

213
00:14:15,650 --> 00:14:18,640
Mike hit my mom with a car.
麦克开车撞到我妈

214
00:14:21,120 --> 00:14:25,080
- No, I didn't. - That's okay. I have forgiven you.
-才没，我没有 -没关系，我已经原谅你了

215
00:14:25,260 --> 00:14:27,520
Now we're friends again, and everything's great.
现在我们又是朋友了 一切都很美好

216
00:14:27,730 --> 00:14:29,460
Well, wait. Is your mom okay?
等一下，你妈还好吧？

217
00:14:29,630 --> 00:14:33,500
Please, we're trying to have a conversation.
拜托，我们在讲话耶

218
00:14:34,670 --> 00:14:36,860
You're a lot nicer on Days of Our Lives.
你在《我们的日子》中亲切多了

219
00:14:37,040 --> 00:14:39,630
Days of Our Lives! That's why you look so familiar!
《我们的日子》！ 怪不得你看起来有点眼熟！

220
00:14:39,810 --> 00:14:40,900
- What? - What?
-什么？ -什么？

221
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:43,200
What?
什么？

222
00:14:43,780 --> 00:14:46,510
Do you not know each other?
你们彼此不认识吗？

223
00:14:47,850 --> 00:14:53,310
Of course we do. He's playing a game we used to play in high school.
我们当然认识 他是在玩我们高中常玩的游戏

224
00:14:53,490 --> 00:14:56,820
We pretend we don't know each other. We played all kinds of games.
我们假装不认识 我们玩很多种游戏的

225
00:14:56,990 --> 00:15:01,430
You remember that one where I punch you in the face for not being cool?
你还记得有一次 你因为太蠢而被我揍吗？

226
00:15:03,030 --> 00:15:06,800
Let me ask you something: How many sisters does Joey have?
让我问你一个问题 乔伊有几个姐妹呢？

227
00:15:06,970 --> 00:15:09,870
- Six. - No, he doesn't. He has seven.
-六个 -不，他有七个

228
00:15:10,040 --> 00:15:12,510
What are you doing? I said seven!
你在搞什么鬼？我比了七个！

229
00:15:15,810 --> 00:15:19,070
Joey, why did you set me up with a stranger?
乔伊，为什么你要介绍陌生人给我呢？

230
00:15:19,250 --> 00:15:23,240
Because I forgot about our date. I'm so sorry.
因为我忘记了，我很抱歉

231
00:15:23,420 --> 00:15:27,820
I'm sorry too. And just to be clear, I didn't hit his mother with a car.
我也很抱歉，还有要澄清一下 我没有开车撞他妈

232
00:15:28,160 --> 00:15:30,180
Although I'd like to be hit by one right now.
不过我现在真的很想被车撞一下

233
00:15:30,360 --> 00:15:31,720
Yeah, no problem.
是喔，没问题

234
00:15:33,390 --> 00:15:38,090
You are unbelievable. I spent so much time finding the perfect girl for you.
你真是太不应该了 我花这么多时间帮你找完美的对象

235
00:15:38,300 --> 00:15:41,290
Mary Ellen is really smart and cute and loose.
犸莉艾伦真的很聪明 很可爱又很随便

236
00:15:41,573 --> 00:15:43,063
嘿！

237
00:15:43,540 --> 00:15:46,170
Who are you kidding?
你别装了吧？

238
00:15:50,440 --> 00:15:53,500
You find some guy off the street for me?
你在街上随便捉个男的塞给我？

239
00:15:53,680 --> 00:15:55,740
God, this is humiliating!
天啊，这真是太羞辱人了！

240
00:15:55,920 --> 00:16:00,010
I'm so sorry. If you don't like this guy, I can find you a better one.
我很抱歉，如果你不喜欢这一个 我可以帮你找更好的

241
00:16:00,190 --> 00:16:02,950
Mike? Mike?
麦克？麦克？

242
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:05,150
I'm out of here.
我要走了

243
00:16:05,630 --> 00:16:07,490
It was nice meeting you.
很高兴认识你

244
00:16:07,660 --> 00:16:10,990
- You're leaving too? - I'll stay if you can tell me my name.
-你也要走？ -你说的出我的名字，我就留下

245
00:16:11,170 --> 00:16:12,390
Have a good night.
再见

246
00:16:16,640 --> 00:16:19,470
We leave tomorrow, and you still have a lot to pack.
我们明天就要走了 而你还有好多东西要打包

247
00:16:19,640 --> 00:16:20,800
You're right.
你说得对

248
00:16:21,710 --> 00:16:23,470
Maybe I shouldn't go.
或许我不应该去

249
00:16:24,650 --> 00:16:26,640
What?
什么？

250
00:16:27,050 --> 00:16:31,510
So Nancy told me about this job at this great restaurant, Javu?
南西告诉我有一个 很棒的餐厅在征人，杰屋？

251
00:16:31,690 --> 00:16:33,950
But it's just a little outside of Tulsa.
离土尔沙不会太远

252
00:16:34,120 --> 00:16:35,450
Well, how far outside?
那是多远呢？

253
00:16:36,320 --> 00:16:37,810
Manhattan?
曼哈顿远吗？

254
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:43,020
And you're thinking of taking it?
你要接受这份工作吗？

255
00:16:44,800 --> 00:16:48,360
Before, you said that being with me was more important than any job.
你之前说跟我在一起 比任何工作都重要

256
00:16:48,540 --> 00:16:53,470
But I guess now it's old job, me, new job.
但我猜，现在是 旧工作，我，新工作

257
00:16:54,810 --> 00:16:56,970
I'm gonna miss this hand!
我会想念这只手的！

258
00:16:59,010 --> 00:17:00,710
I know this is a lot to ask..
我知道这很过份…

259
00:17:00,880 --> 00:17:03,910
but, my God, this is a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity.
但是，天啊，这是千载难逢的好机会

260
00:17:04,080 --> 00:17:07,080
What happened to "you can't live without me four days a week"?
那你说无法忍受每星期四天 要分开，是怎么回事呢？

261
00:17:07,250 --> 00:17:12,350
Well, if you really think about it, I mean, four days is not that long.
如果你仔细想想 四天并不是很长的时间

262
00:17:12,530 --> 00:17:14,390
I see you Monday before you go to work..
星期一你去上班前我会见到你…

263
00:17:14,560 --> 00:17:16,260
and Thursday when you get back..
然后星期四晚上我也会见到你…

264
00:17:16,460 --> 00:17:20,190
and I always work late on Tuesdays, so really if you think about it..
而我总是在星期二忙得很晚 所以如果你仔细想想…

265
00:17:20,370 --> 00:17:21,770
it's really just one day.
事实上只有分开一天而已

266
00:17:21,970 --> 00:17:26,960
And well, if we can't make it one day, we got real problems, my friend.
而如果我们连一天都撑不住 我们真的是有大问题了

267
00:17:31,080 --> 00:17:34,240
- I think you should take the job. - Really?
-我认为你应该接受这份工作 -真的吗？

268
00:17:34,420 --> 00:17:38,510
I know it must be important to you when you start chattering like a monkey.
当你开始像猴子一样鬼吼时 我就知道这对你一定很重要

269
00:17:40,750 --> 00:17:43,590
That's the nicest thing anybody's ever said to me.
这是我听过最美好的形容了

270
00:17:43,760 --> 00:17:45,990
It's your dream job. I can't make you pass it up.
这是你的梦想工作 我不能要求你放弃的

271
00:17:46,160 --> 00:17:47,920
Besides, I'm proud of you.
况且我还以你为荣

272
00:17:48,100 --> 00:17:49,620
- You are? - Yeah.
-真的吗？ -是啊

273
00:17:49,800 --> 00:17:52,700
And when I get to Tulsa and people say, "Where's the missus"..
当我去到土尔沙，有人问我 “你老婆呢？”

274
00:17:52,870 --> 00:17:55,160
I'll tell them she's a chef at Javu.
我会告诉他们，她在杰屋当主厨

275
00:17:55,940 --> 00:17:58,700
And then, when they stare at me blankly..
然后，当他们 搞不清状况盯着我看时…

276
00:17:58,870 --> 00:18:03,100
I'll make some offensive Tulsa joke, and thus, begin my isolation.
我就会说一些污辱土尔沙的笑话 然后开始被他们排挤

277
00:18:07,820 --> 00:18:10,840
- How was the pediatrician? - I really liked him.
-新医生怎样呢？ -我真的很喜欢他

278
00:18:11,020 --> 00:18:15,680
Yeah, yeah. It was really, really, really good.
是啊，是啊 真的，真的，真的很不错

279
00:18:15,990 --> 00:18:19,480
- You promised not to say anything. - I know.
-你答应我不会说出去的 -我知道

280
00:18:19,660 --> 00:18:22,890
Ross still sees his pediatrician!
罗斯还在看他小时候的医生！

281
00:18:24,500 --> 00:18:26,690
I don't care.
我不在乎

282
00:18:27,600 --> 00:18:30,870
Are you serious? You still see Dr. Gettleman?
真的吗？ 你还在看葛曼医师？

283
00:18:31,040 --> 00:18:33,010
He is a brilliant diagnostician!
他是医术高明的诊断师！

284
00:18:33,170 --> 00:18:36,900
Diagnostician or boo-boo fixer?
诊断师还是医生叔叔呢？

285
00:18:37,580 --> 00:18:40,100
Seriously, you gotta go to an appropriate doctor.
真的，你应该去看适合你的医生才对

286
00:18:40,280 --> 00:18:43,150
And not an orthodontist..
不是牙科医生…

287
00:18:43,320 --> 00:18:46,380
not a gynecologist..
不是妇科医生…

288
00:18:46,550 --> 00:18:49,420
and not a veterinarian..
也更不是兽医

289
00:18:49,620 --> 00:18:53,790
Why? I know it's a little weird, but he is a great doctor, okay?
为什么？我知道这是有点怪 但是他是个很棒的医生，好吗？

290
00:18:53,960 --> 00:18:55,690
He knows my medical history.
他知道我的病史

291
00:18:55,900 --> 00:18:58,760
And every time I go in there, he makes a big deal.
而且每次我去看病 他都非常的慎重其事

292
00:18:58,930 --> 00:19:01,460
You know, "Look, it's my favorite patient."
你知道的 “瞧，这是我最喜欢的病人”

293
00:19:01,640 --> 00:19:05,300
Does he say that before he sticks his thermometer in your tushy?
是不是在把体温计 插到你嘴里之前说的呢？

294
00:19:05,470 --> 00:19:10,140
I seem to remember someone bringing his security blanket to college.
我还记得有人把他的 安全毛毯带到大学宿舍

295
00:19:10,310 --> 00:19:13,210
That was not a security blanket. That was a wall hanging.
那不是安全毛毯 那是壁毯

296
00:19:13,410 --> 00:19:15,470
It didn't spend much time on the wall!
它倒是没有被挂在墙上太久！

297
00:19:25,630 --> 00:19:27,490
Excuse me.
对不起

298
00:19:28,230 --> 00:19:31,690
Hi. I was hoping to run into you. Can we talk?
嗨，我原本就希望可以再遇到你 我们可以谈谈吗？

299
00:19:32,100 --> 00:19:33,290
Sure.
当然

300
00:19:33,930 --> 00:19:36,100
Yeah. There's someone I want you to meet.
我想要介绍你认识一个人

301
00:19:36,270 --> 00:19:39,430
This is my best friend from high school.
这位是我高中最要好的朋友

302
00:19:41,180 --> 00:19:43,270
I'm sorry, I don't think I know you.
很抱歉，我并不认识你

303
00:19:43,440 --> 00:19:45,070
How hard was that?
真是太容易了

304
00:19:46,050 --> 00:19:49,710
Look, I'm sorry, really. I'm so embarrassed.
我真的很抱歉 我实在太不好意思了

305
00:19:51,520 --> 00:19:53,080
Please.
拜托

306
00:19:53,320 --> 00:19:58,350
Really, I'm a pretty nice guy. Just ask my parole officer.
真的，我是个还不错的人 你可以问我的保释官

307
00:20:01,300 --> 00:20:04,730
Apparently, I'm not a funny guy.
很明显地，我并不是很风趣

308
00:20:06,170 --> 00:20:09,470
Well, why did you go along with that?
那你为什么要这样做呢？

309
00:20:09,640 --> 00:20:14,870
Because I was told that I'd get a free dinner, which I didn't.
因为他说，我可以吃一顿 免费的晚餐，不过并没有

310
00:20:15,040 --> 00:20:18,270
And that I'd meet a pretty girl, which I did.
还有他说，我可以认识 漂亮的女生，这倒是有

311
00:20:20,650 --> 00:20:22,770
That's true.
那倒是真的

312
00:20:25,890 --> 00:20:28,480
Well, is anything you told me about yourself true?
那你告诉我的事有哪些是真的呢？

313
00:20:28,660 --> 00:20:31,650
My name is Mike. And I do play piano.
我的名字真的是麦克 还有我真的会弹钢琴

314
00:20:31,830 --> 00:20:35,590
- Prove it. - There isn't a piano here.
-证明给我看 -这里并没有钢琴

315
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:39,360
That wouldn't stand in the way of a true pianist.
那对真正的钢琴家不会是问题吧

316
00:20:40,100 --> 00:20:41,500
Okay.
好吧

317
00:20:57,950 --> 00:20:59,540
You are really good.
你真的很棒

318
00:21:03,960 --> 00:21:07,390
- I play a little guitar myself. - Really? That's great.
-我会弹一点吉他 -真的？太棒了

319
00:21:07,560 --> 00:21:11,220
- What kind of music do you play? - Like acoustic, folksy stuff, you know?
-你弹奏什么种音乐呢？ -像是重原音、有民俗风味的

320
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:16,270
But right now I'm working on a couple lron Maiden covers.
但是我现在在制作CD封面

321
00:21:17,840 --> 00:21:23,470
Do you think that, maybe, sometime, I could..
你想，或许，有空的话，我可…

322
00:21:23,640 --> 00:21:26,080
It's okay. Go ahead, ask me out.
没关系的，来吧，约我吧

323
00:21:27,480 --> 00:21:31,210
Okay. You think, maybe, sometime I could take you out?
好吧，你想，或许有空的话 我可以约你出去吗？

324
00:21:31,890 --> 00:21:34,080
You just caught me off guard.
你真是让我一点心理准备都没有

325
00:21:35,220 --> 00:21:37,020
Yeah, that would be nice.
好啊，我很乐意

326
00:21:37,220 --> 00:21:39,850
Look at this! My two best friends!
瞧瞧！我两个最要好的朋友！

327
00:21:47,400 --> 00:21:50,200
Excuse me. I don't mean to be a jerk..
不好意思，我不想要太机车…

328
00:21:50,370 --> 00:21:53,900
but the baby with the rash came in after me.
但是那个长疹子的婴儿 是在我后面进来的

329
00:21:54,740 --> 00:21:57,540
- The doctor will be right with you, sir. - I hear you..
-医生等一下就可以看你了，先生 -我知道…

330
00:21:57,710 --> 00:21:59,840
but do you have any harder puzzles?
但是你有没有比较高难度的谜题呢？

331
00:22:05,720 --> 00:22:07,780
Mommy, I can't find Waldo.
妈咪，我找不到华多

332
00:22:07,950 --> 00:22:09,480
What page are you on?
你在第几页呢？

333
00:22:09,660 --> 00:22:12,090
What, the circus? He's behind the elephant.
游乐场吗？他在大象后面

334
00:22:12,260 --> 00:22:15,990
Wow. So your child's a big fan of the Waldo books too?
哇，你的孩子一定也很迷华多

335
00:22:18,370 --> 00:22:21,390
Yeah, that's how I know.
是啊，所以我也很熟

336
00:22:22,100 --> 00:22:25,090
- I'm Ross, by the way. - Hi, I'm Sally.
-对了，我叫罗斯 -嗨，我叫莎莉

337
00:22:25,270 --> 00:22:29,070
So no ring. Can I assume you're also a single parent?
没有戒指，所以我推想你也是单亲？

338
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:33,010
- I am a single parent. - It's hard, isn't it?
-我是单亲没错 -很难，对吧？

339
00:22:33,180 --> 00:22:36,670
There's no time for a social life. Where are you gonna meet someone?
根本没有可以社交的时间 要去哪里认识朋友呢？

340
00:22:36,850 --> 00:22:38,440
- Well.. - Mommy, I can't..
-那个… -妈咪，我找不…

341
00:22:38,620 --> 00:22:40,780
Sea shore? Row boat.
海边吗？在小船上

342
00:22:44,390 --> 00:22:49,450
Let's say, I don't know, you met someone in the pediatrician's office.
我想，我不知道 可以在小儿科医生那里认识人吧

343
00:22:50,730 --> 00:22:53,100
Rossie? We're ready for you.
小罗斯？轮到你了

344
00:23:01,510 --> 00:23:03,000
Yeah..
是啊…

345
00:23:05,080 --> 00:23:09,110
Come on, Ross Jr. It's time to go in.
走吧，小罗斯 轮到我们了

346
00:23:10,450 --> 00:23:12,440
Mommy.
妈咪

347
00:23:16,390 --> 00:23:18,480
Mommy, what's wrong with that man?
妈咪，那个人是怎么了？

348
00:23:18,660 --> 00:23:21,020
Hey, I helped you find Waldo!
嘿，是我帮你找到华多的耶！

349
00:23:28,600 --> 00:23:31,730
- Good, you haven't left yet. - Where have you been?
-太好了，你还没走 -你去哪了？

350
00:23:31,910 --> 00:23:35,310
I got held up at Dr. Gettleman's office.
有事情在葛曼医师那耽搁了一下

351
00:23:35,510 --> 00:23:40,210
There was some guy that freaked everybody out.
有一个人吓坏了所有的人

352
00:23:40,410 --> 00:23:43,410
I don't think I'm going back there.
我想我再也不要回去那里了

353
00:23:43,620 --> 00:23:46,310
You got here just in time. I really have to go, buddy.
你正好赶上 我得要走了，兄弟

354
00:23:46,490 --> 00:23:47,510
Oh, man.
喔，真是的

355
00:23:47,690 --> 00:23:51,520
- Promise to call me when you land? - Of course I will. I love you.
-答应我一下飞机就打电话 -当然，我爱你

356
00:23:51,690 --> 00:23:52,850
I love you too.
我也爱你

357
00:23:58,000 --> 00:24:01,900
Watch the tongue, people. We got a baby over here.
不要舌吻，你们，儿童不宜

358
00:24:02,400 --> 00:24:05,240
- Bye, Chandler. - Bye.
-再见，钱德 -再见

359
00:24:05,410 --> 00:24:07,770
- Bye, honey. - Bye.
-再见，亲爱的 -再见

360
00:24:12,180 --> 00:24:16,010
- What's the matter, Joe? - I'm mad at you for leaving.
-怎么了，乔伊？ -我很生气你要走

361
00:24:16,180 --> 00:24:19,980
You know, you're nothing but a big leaver.
你知道吗？你什么都不会 就最会抛弃人家

362
00:24:20,290 --> 00:24:23,690
A big leaver with a stupid suitcase.
带着笨行李的负心汉

363
00:24:25,590 --> 00:24:30,390
Any chance you're trying to pick a fight to make all of this easier?
你是不是故意说一些气话 让自己好过点呢？

364
00:24:33,170 --> 00:24:36,400
Dude, you see right through me!
老兄，你真是太了解我了！

365
00:24:45,310 --> 00:24:47,710
Okay, well.. Bye, Mon.
好了，那么…再见了，摩妮卡

366
00:24:48,380 --> 00:24:50,410
Bye, Ross. Rachel.
再见，罗斯，瑞秋

367
00:24:51,020 --> 00:24:54,180
- Bye, Emma. - Okay, bye-bye.
-再见，艾犸 -好了，拜拜

368
00:24:54,350 --> 00:24:57,550
Have a good trip. Okay. Oh, my God.
旅途愉快，好了，喔，天啊

369
00:25:01,700 --> 00:25:03,530
Wait.
钱德，等一下

370
00:25:04,930 --> 00:25:07,900
It goes old job..
应该是旧工作…

371
00:25:08,070 --> 00:25:10,130
new job..
新工作…

372
00:25:10,340 --> 00:25:11,530
and you.
然后是你

373
00:25:13,640 --> 00:25:15,700
This is just something I have to do.
那只不过是我要做的工作

374
00:25:16,240 --> 00:25:18,300
I know.
我知道

375
00:25:18,480 --> 00:25:20,810
I love you so much.
我好爱你

376
00:25:20,980 --> 00:25:23,610
I know that too.
我也知道

377
00:25:34,090 --> 00:25:37,930
Don't worry. I'll be back before you know it.
别担心 我很快就会回来了

378
00:25:38,100 --> 00:25:39,860
Yes, it will be the same.
是的，一切都不会变

379
00:25:40,630 --> 00:25:43,230
Because I know, that's how.
因为我就是知道

380
00:25:43,400 --> 00:25:44,460
I promise.
我保证

381
00:25:44,640 --> 00:25:45,970
You double promise?
你可以双重保证吗？

382
00:25:50,610 --> 00:25:52,240
Call me when you land.
一下机就打电话给我

383
00:25:53,810 --> 00:25:56,180
- Can I talk now? - Okay, bye.
-轮到我讲了吗？ -好的，再见

384
00:25:56,380 --> 00:25:58,210
- Joey! - He had to board.
-乔伊！ -他要登机了

385
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000


